(thirdQuint)Wearable Cardioverter Defibrillator in Hemodialysis Patients (WED-HED) Study.

 Objective: To study the impact of wearable cardioverter defibrillator (WCD) use on sudden cardiac death in hemodialysis patients.

 Study Population: Participants will be patients beginning hemodialysis ( 50 years old.

 Intervention: A WCD will be used for protection against sudden cardiac death (SCD).

 Study Design: The study will be a multi-center, prospective, randomized controlled trial with 1:1 assignment of treatment and control.

 Study Size: The study will enroll up to 2,600 subjects.

 A maximum of 200 sites will be used for enrollment.

